Titolo: The Arcade Machine

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: The Arcade Machine is a game creation system written by Chris  Jochumson and Doug Carlston for the Apple II and published by Broderbund in 1982. Louis Ewens ported it to the Atari 8-bit family. Broderbund ran a contest from Januaryâ€“June 1984 where the best user-created game was awarded a prize of $1,500 in hardware and software. Jochumson also wrote Track Attack for Broderbund.

Genere: Game creation system

Valutazione: 58
